<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                        <head>284. Memorandum for the record, May 17<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d284fn1">Review of Operation Mongoose. Secret. 1 p. <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_DCI_1">DCI</gloss> (<persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">McCone</persName>)
                                Files: Job 91–00741R, Box 1, Mongoose Papers.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1962-05-17">May 17, 1962</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d284-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d284-1"/>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital">Memorandum of Review of Operation
                            Mongoose—Thursday, May 17th</p>
                        <p>General <persName corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName> reported on
                            the operations, submitting a written statement of even date covering
                            operations from May 11th to 17th.</p>
                        <p>There was no discussion of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HWK_1">Harvey</persName>’s report on TV intrusions of May 16th except to
                            the extent commented in the <persName corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName> report.</p>
                        <p>General <persName corresp="#p_LBGEG_1">Lansdale</persName> submitted a
                            new schedule of priority operations for the period May 21st to June
                            30th. The schedule was accepted by the Special Group for review and
                            study and decision at the meeting on Thursday, May 24th.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed corresp="#p_MJA_1"><persName corresp="#p_MJA_1">John A.
                                    McCone</persName></signed>
                            <affiliation>Director</affiliation>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>